article.description: — Tyon Grant-Foster had 21 points in Grand Canyon's 76-69 victory over UT Arlington on Saturday night.
article.headline: Grant-Foster scores 21, Grand Canyon beats UT Arlington 76-69
article.linkText: Grant-Foster scores 21, Grand Canyon beats UT Arlington 76-69
article.story: PHOENIX -- — Tyon Grant-Foster had 21 points in Grand Canyon's 76-69 victory over UT Arlington on Saturday night. Grant-Foster added 10 rebounds and three steals for the Antelopes (6-1). Gabe McGlothan scored 16 points while going 6 of 10 from the floor, including 2 for 4 from 3-point range, and 2 for 4 from the line, and added nine rebounds. Rayshon Harrison shot 3 for 11 (1 for 4 from 3-point range) and 4 of 5 from the free throw line to finish with 11 points, while adding three steals. The Mavericks (4-4) were led in scoring by Fabio Basili, who finished with 15 points. UT Arlington also got 10 points and eight rebounds from Dwayne Koroma. DaJuan Gordon also had 10 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
